        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-06-04 15:29:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nHi Sebastien, we are in progress of landing SMP patches for LNet, and this one should also resolve this problem: http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,2725\n\nSo we might not land this patch to master, but I think we can land it to 2.1.x and 2.2.x because we are not going to backport and SMP patches to earlier version.\n\nThanks",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "67fe89e1a4821fd2c1e21b3a58bac53f138729f6",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 160,
        "name": "Sebastien Buisson",
        "email": "sebastien.buisson@bull.net",
        "username": "sebastien.buisson",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-06-06 14:37:33.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nHi Liang,\n\nYou are right, your patch does the same thing, plus many others ;-)\nGiven that it is part of a large set of patches bringing SMP scalability to master, I understand it will not be possible to port it to former branches.\n\nFor that purpose, I have created a b2_1 version of my patch accessible here: http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,3047\nand also a b2_2 version here: http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,3044",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
